# Release Management & Workflow

**Reference**: See `learning-docs/strategies/release-strategy.md` for complete details.

## Release Timeline & Milestones

```
v0.1.0 → Phase 1a + 1b (Button, IconButton, FAB, TextField, Checkbox, Switch)
v0.2.0 → + Phase 2 (Navigation: AppBar, Tabs, Drawer)
v0.3.0 → + Phase 3 (Feedback: Dialog, Snackbar, Menu)
v1.0.0 → Stable Release (All phases complete, API frozen)
```

## Semantic Versioning

**Pre-1.0 (v0.x.x):**
- `v0.x.0` → New features (minor version bump)
- `v0.x.y` → Bug fixes (patch version bump)
- Breaking changes ALLOWED (document in CHANGELOG)

**Post-1.0 (v1.x.x):**
- `v1.0.0` → First stable release (API frozen)
- `v1.x.0` → New features (backward compatible)
- `v1.0.x` → Bug fixes only
- `v2.0.0` → Breaking changes

## Branch Strategy

**Primary Branches:**
- **`main`** - Production releases ONLY (protected, tagged)
- **`dev`** - Integration branch (protected, default for PRs)

**Feature Branch Format**: `type/phase-component-description`

| Type | Format | Example |
|------|--------|---------|
| Feature | `feat/phase-name` | `feat/1b-textfield-component` |
| Bug Fix | `fix/description` | `fix/button-disabled-state` |
| Docs | `docs/description` | `docs/button-storybook-examples` |
| Refactor | `refactor/description` | `refactor/tokens-color-system` |
| Test | `test/description` | `test/button-accessibility-tests` |
| Hotfix | `hotfix/vX.X.X-description` | `hotfix/v0.1.1-button-crash` |

## Quality Gate Checklist

Before ANY commit:
- [ ] All tests passing (`pnpm test`)
- [ ] No linter errors (`pnpm lint`)
- [ ] No TypeScript errors (`pnpm typecheck`)
- [ ] Code follows three-layer architecture
- [ ] 85%+ test coverage maintained

Before ANY push:
- [ ] All commits use conventional format
- [ ] Task completion documentation created
- [ ] Storybook stories added and verified

## Release Process

At release milestones (e.g., v0.1.0):

1. Version bump with Changesets or manual
2. CHANGELOG.md update
3. Create release branch (`release/v0.1.0`)
4. Final quality checks
5. Merge to `main` (no squash)
6. Tag release (`git tag -a v0.1.0`)
7. GitHub release creation
8. NPM publishing
9. Sync `dev` with `main`
